===Proper noun===
'''Abdullah'''

# A given name, meaning 'servant of [[Allah]]' in Arabic. It is a common Islamic name that is favored because it indicates servitude and humility before God. According to the a [[Hadith]], "The most beloved of your names to Allah - the Mighty and Magnificent - are 'Abdullah' and 'Abdur-Rahman' (servant of the Most Merciful)", the name is also was favourble to the [[Prophet]] [[Muhammad]].

